WEBVTT

1
00:01:09.792 --> 00:01:12.083 line:82%
NEVER SAY GOODBYE

2
00:03:38.125 --> 00:03:41.833 line:82%
Maya... Maya, come on hurry up.
The groom will be here at one.

3
00:03:53.417 --> 00:03:57.583 line:82%
Yes, I'm married and I also have a son.
But just to make it clear,

4
00:03:57.667 --> 00:04:00.625 line:82%
I keep my personal life
and professional life separate.

5
00:04:03.042 --> 00:04:05.667 line:82%
But our fashion magazine needs
a lot of time.

6
00:04:06.292 --> 00:04:09.292 line:82%
Your magazine does not need time.
It needs me.

7
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:33.917 line:82%
Dad. Dad!

8
00:05:46.125 --> 00:05:49.208 line:82%
God, dad... And how did this break?

9
00:05:51.583 --> 00:05:53.708 line:82%
I'll teach you how. I will.

10
00:06:17.292 --> 00:06:19.083 line:82%
Dad, I'm getting married today and you...

11
00:06:19.917 --> 00:06:21.000 line:82%
What do I do, my son?

12
00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:24.000 line:82%
Before dying your Mom made me
promise that after she goes...

13
00:06:24.583 --> 00:06:27.417 line:82%
I should do all that I never did
while she was alive...

14
00:06:27.500 --> 00:06:29.167 line:82%
I'm just fulfilling my promise...

15
00:06:30.167 --> 00:06:32.417 line:82%
And what about the promise I made to Maya?
Can I fulfill that?

16
00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:33.620 line:82%
-Why not?
-Can we go?

17
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:35.000 line:82%
Just a minute... just a minute...

18
00:06:37.625 --> 00:06:38.458 line:82%
This is from me.

19
00:06:40.125 --> 00:06:41.125 line:82%
And this from your Mom.

20
00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:44.917 line:82%
God bless you, son. Be happy.

21
00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:04.958 line:82%
What is this noise? I can't hear a thing.

22
00:07:05.458 --> 00:07:11.458 line:82%
Nothing... Nothing at all.
Just a small match that we won.

23
00:07:14.083 --> 00:07:15.958 line:82%
I'm so sorry. I forgot completely.

24
00:07:16.417 --> 00:07:18.833 line:82%
Rhea, I'm your husband
just don't forget that.

25
00:07:22.250 --> 00:07:23.458 line:82%
Tell me, how was it?

26
00:07:23.958 --> 00:07:27.375 line:82%
Fantastic. My last goal.
all that tension, excitement.

27
00:07:28.125 --> 00:07:31.000 line:82%
Rhea... Rhea, you should have been here.

28
00:07:32.375 --> 00:07:33.792 line:82%
But I had an interview.

29
00:07:37.167 --> 00:07:38.000 line:82%
You know what?

30
00:07:38.292 --> 00:07:41.250 line:82%
We'll fix up the next match after
checking with your busy schedule.

31
00:07:42.667 --> 00:07:44.208 line:82%
And if you have the time

32
00:07:44.292 --> 00:07:46.792 line:82%
just have a look at my five million
dollar contract.

33
00:07:47.042 --> 00:07:48.583 line:82%
Five million dollars?

34
00:07:49.333 --> 00:07:52.000 line:82%
Why? Jealous?
That now I earn more than you?

35
00:07:52.208 --> 00:07:56.083 line:82%
Not jealous baby. Happy.
Happy that your dream has come true.

36
00:07:57.417 --> 00:07:58.333 line:82%
Our dream, Rhea.

37
00:07:59.375 --> 00:08:02.958 line:82%
Yeah, I know. By the way,
I'm going to fetch Arjun from school.

38
00:08:03.167 --> 00:08:04.833 line:82%
will you please fetch Mom
from the wedding?

39
00:08:05.917 --> 00:08:07.083 line:82%
I completely forgot that...

40
00:08:07.167 --> 00:08:08.000 line:82%
What's the matter, Rhea?

41
00:08:08.083 --> 00:08:09.083 line:82%
You seem to be forgetting
a lot these days.

42
00:08:36.917 --> 00:08:40.958 line:82%
Today I'm going to part with my daughter
and get a daughter-in-law home.

43
00:08:50.833 --> 00:08:52.833 line:82%
It's taken her three years to say 'yes'.

44
00:08:53.458 --> 00:08:54.750 line:82%
She won't run away at the last minute,
will she?

45
00:08:54.833 --> 00:08:56.625 line:82%
No... No, she can't run away anywhere.

46
00:08:57.708 --> 00:08:59.833 line:82%
Yeah. After all where will she
find a husband like me, right?

47
00:09:00.167 --> 00:09:02.000 line:82%
No, our security is very tight.

48
00:09:11.750 --> 00:09:15.000 line:82%
-Who Suzie?
-Not Suzie. Give it to me, come on. Go.

49
00:09:16.542 --> 00:09:18.708 line:82%
They'll drive me mad.
all the idiots from New York--

50
00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.583 line:82%
-That scared me.
-Didn't mean to.

51
00:09:30.708 --> 00:09:33.167 line:82%
I'm Sam. And welcome to my humble home.

52
00:09:33.292 --> 00:09:35.375 line:82%
I'm Kamal, and this is my food.

53
00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:43.333 line:82%
Wow. Definitely a
Sardarni.

54
00:09:43.792 --> 00:09:45.042 line:82%
How did you know that?

55
00:09:45.292 --> 00:09:47.375 line:82%
Because I have been fed
and slapped by them.

56
00:09:48.667 --> 00:09:51.208 line:82%
I know.
I have heard a lot about you.

57
00:09:51.417 --> 00:09:52.917 line:82%
Don't go by what others say.

58
00:09:53.208 --> 00:09:55.417 line:82%
But all that's said is always
by others, Mr. Talwar.

59
00:09:55.750 --> 00:09:57.958 line:82%
Whose word does one go by then?

60
00:09:58.083 --> 00:10:02.375 line:82%
Mine. My word.
You are from Chandigarh.

61
00:10:03.625 --> 00:10:05.417 line:82%
And how did you figure that out?

62
00:10:14.958 --> 00:10:16.583 line:82%
Mom. What are you doing?

63
00:10:17.917 --> 00:10:19.417 line:82%
Just. Nothing.

64
00:10:20.792 --> 00:10:23.292 line:82%
No, I don't know what's taking
the bride so long.

65
00:10:23.708 --> 00:10:25.000 line:82%
You carry on. I'll come on my own.

66
00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:41.167 line:82%
Please don't mess the garden.

67
00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:42.500 line:82%
I have just cleaned it up.

68
00:10:43.583 --> 00:10:45.250 line:82%
-Are you the gardener?
-What do you think?

69
00:10:45.792 --> 00:10:48.042 line:82%
I think you have
stolen the bride's clothes.

70
00:10:48.125 --> 00:10:48.958 line:82%
Should I inform inside?

71
00:10:52.500 --> 00:10:55.375 line:82%
It's your wedding
and you are sitting outside here. Why?

72
00:10:55.792 --> 00:10:56.792 line:82%
Do you have a problem?

73
00:10:56.875 --> 00:11:00.542 line:82%
Not directly. But indirectly I do.
My mother has a problem.

74
00:11:01.042 --> 00:11:04.625 line:82%
The faster you go inside,
the faster my mother can leave from here.

75
00:11:05.458 --> 00:11:07.167 line:82%
You are a strange man.
You sat down?

76
00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:08.750 line:82%
Should I lie down and chat?

77
00:11:09.542 --> 00:11:11.292 line:82%
One to one discussions
always happen while seated.

78
00:11:11.750 --> 00:11:12.958 line:82%
Discussion?

79
00:11:13.375 --> 00:11:14.500 line:82%
Yes. I know you have a problem.

80
00:11:17.208 --> 00:11:19.250 line:82%
Why should I discuss my problem with you?

81
00:11:19.333 --> 00:11:20.833 line:82%
So, you admit you have a problem.

82
00:11:23.625 --> 00:11:25.667 line:82%
By the way, I don't take
advice from anyone.

83
00:11:26.042 --> 00:11:28.042 line:82%
But I'm always ready
to give advice to others.

84
00:11:28.625 --> 00:11:31.458 line:82%
You should always listen to strangers.

85
00:11:33.125 --> 00:11:36.833 line:82%
Sometimes they know better than our own.

86
00:11:39.208 --> 00:11:40.250 line:82%
Are you married?

87
00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:47.250 line:82%
It's five years today.

88
00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:49.750 line:82%
What did you think before marrying?

89
00:11:50.750 --> 00:11:53.375 line:82%
Who thinks before marrying?

90
00:11:59.917 --> 00:12:02.958 line:82%
Rhea and me, are friends from college.

91
00:12:03.708 --> 00:12:06.458 line:82%
So we thought we'd give our
friendship a new meaning.

92
00:12:07.500 --> 00:12:13.167 line:82%
Besides what can be better than spending
your entire life with your friend?

93
00:12:15.667 --> 00:12:20.833 line:82%
At times friendship replaces love and
then there's no space left for love.

94
00:12:25.458 --> 00:12:28.250 line:82%
By the way, the guy
waiting for you inside,

95
00:12:29.167 --> 00:12:31.458 line:82%
is he your friend or your love?

96
00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:36.333 line:82%
You can't take that long.

97
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:40.000 line:82%
I have known Rishi since childhood.

98
00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:45.167 line:82%
After my parents died, Rishi
and his father have been my family.

99
00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:47.958 line:82%
What a sweet family.

100
00:12:48.375 --> 00:12:51.333 line:82%
But that's not the answer
to my question. Do you love him?

101
00:12:54.583 --> 00:13:00.500 line:82%
I do.
But not the way I thought I would.

102
00:13:01.333 --> 00:13:05.375 line:82%
like how? like in good books and bad films
That kind of love?

103
00:13:06.292 --> 00:13:11.208 line:82%
No. The way love ought to be.
That kind of love.

104
00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:13.625 line:82%
That kind of love.
But where does it exist anymore?

105
00:13:14.417 --> 00:13:15.250 line:82%
listen to this.

106
00:13:16.750 --> 00:13:21.208 line:82%
'The sagas of everlasting romances
have gone past long ago.

107
00:13:22.292 --> 00:13:24.208 line:82%
Just learn to make do
with tiny love stories.'

108
00:13:27.833 --> 00:13:32.042 line:82%
Does that mean you don't love your wife?

109
00:13:37.583 --> 00:13:38.542 line:82%
You can't take that long.

110
00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:46.708 line:82%
We are happy.
We have made our little world together.

111
00:13:47.417 --> 00:13:48.833 line:82%
That's not the answer to my question.

112
00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:54.167 line:82%
The question here is more
about your life than my answer.

113
00:13:55.125 --> 00:13:58.750 line:82%
You are at a crossroad in life
where there are two roads.

114
00:13:59.833 --> 00:14:04.500 line:82%
One that leads to happiness,
which I think you deserve

115
00:14:05.292 --> 00:14:06.583 line:82%
and the other that leads
to an endless wait.

116
00:14:07.833 --> 00:14:10.917 line:82%
wait for love.
Which you may never find.

117
00:14:12.458 --> 00:14:14.833 line:82%
What if I find that love after marriage?

118
00:14:17.667 --> 00:14:20.042 line:82%
if you don't look for it,
you won't find it.

119
00:14:23.292 --> 00:14:25.542 line:82%
And you are definitely not finding
it sitting on this bench.

120
00:14:26.625 --> 00:14:27.667 line:82%
Go inside and get married.

121
00:14:27.917 --> 00:14:29.208 line:82%
The wedding is waiting for you.

122
00:14:29.292 --> 00:14:32.042 line:82%
and here you are sitting
with a stranger making small talk.

123
00:14:32.250 --> 00:14:33.417 line:82%
You should be ashamed.
What will people say?

124
00:14:50.333 --> 00:14:51.792 line:82%
Now go fast, get married and be happy.

125
00:14:53.667 --> 00:14:54.500 line:82%
Goodbye.

126
00:14:54.583 --> 00:14:59.125 line:82%
Not good bye.
Goodbye kills the hope of meeting again.

127
00:14:59.875 --> 00:15:01.542 line:82%
And who knows?
We may meet again.

128
00:15:22.958 --> 00:15:28.625 line:82%
Just like fragrance merges into breeze.

129
00:15:29.125 --> 00:15:34.417 line:82%
And fades away.

130
00:15:35.583 --> 00:15:41.458 line:82%
Intense moments, with time.

131
00:15:42.042 --> 00:15:47.792 line:82%
Have a way of seeming like dreams.

132
00:15:51.125 --> 00:15:56.167 line:82%
Who knows? We may meet again yet.

133
00:15:57.583 --> 00:16:02.917 line:82%
You should never say goodbye.

134
00:16:03.708 --> 00:16:08.000 line:82%
Never say goodbye.

135
00:16:09.958 --> 00:16:15.167 line:82%
Never say goodbye.

136
00:16:16.208 --> 00:16:21.667 line:82%
Never say goodbye.

137
00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:27.250 line:82%
They say time heals all wounds.

138
00:17:28.250 --> 00:17:34.250 line:82%
But in some relationships,
some wounds only get deeper with time.

139
00:18:12.958 --> 00:18:14.292 line:82%
That's the new fear that stalks New York.

140
00:18:14.583 --> 00:18:17.042 line:82%
Known as the Black Beast,
this dangerous criminal has kidnapped

141
00:18:17.125 --> 00:18:19.000 line:82%
yet another child from central Park.

142
00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:21.292 line:82%
No one knows if it is a man or a woman.

143
00:18:21.625 --> 00:18:23.125 line:82%
He's nicknamed Black Beast

144
00:18:23.208 --> 00:18:26.167 line:82%
because the criminal wears
a trademark long, black coat.

145
00:18:26.458 --> 00:18:29.250 line:82%
Police have asked parents to take
special care of their children.

146
00:18:33.417 --> 00:18:36.250 line:82%
Don't cry my, son.
Don't cry. I'm right here.

147
00:18:40.083 --> 00:18:43.792 line:82%
Sorry, sir. Please don't mind.
My Tinu here is just a little nervous.

148
00:18:43.958 --> 00:18:46.250 line:82%
He thinks the Black Beast
is going to kidnap him.

149
00:18:46.917 --> 00:18:48.958 line:82%
Why should I mind?
My leg's already broken.

150
00:18:49.333 --> 00:18:51.833 line:82%
Tinu, my small, fat little angel.

151
00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:53.750 line:82%
the Black Beast will not kidnap you.

152
00:18:53.833 --> 00:18:55.958 line:82%
To kidnap you he has to lift you first.

153
00:18:56.042 --> 00:18:57.917 line:82%
And have you looked at your weight?

154
00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:02.500 line:82%
My little fatso. Your son's not a child.
he is a bull... bull!

155
00:19:02.583 --> 00:19:03.417 line:82%
What?

156
00:19:03.500 --> 00:19:06.292 line:82%
And with God's blessing
even if he manages to lift him

157
00:19:06.375 --> 00:19:08.000 line:82%
he will die of a heart attack.

158
00:19:08.083 --> 00:19:09.708 line:82%
-Mummy!
-You mean she's still alive?

159
00:19:09.792 --> 00:19:11.333 line:82%
How did she survive
the weight of your father?

160
00:19:11.417 --> 00:19:13.667 line:82%
-How rude!
-Rude? You football field!

161
00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:14.875 line:82%
Just pick this football of yours
and leave right now.

162
00:19:15.125 --> 00:19:16.542 line:82%
Come on. Let's go.
We don't want to sit here.

163
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:17.667 line:82%
Come on, go.
You should have asked before sitting.

164
00:19:17.750 --> 00:19:20.917 line:82%
And by the way, does your entire family
ever fit in a single photograph?

165
00:19:23.917 --> 00:19:24.833 line:82%
Should we go?

166
00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:27.042 line:82%
You know I'll leave when you want to.
What's the need to ask?

167
00:19:28.750 --> 00:19:30.292 line:82%
I just asked a simple question.

168
00:19:30.958 --> 00:19:32.333 line:82%
Even I didn't answer in French.

169
00:19:32.917 --> 00:19:33.750 line:82%
I'm going home.

170
00:19:34.500 --> 00:19:35.583 line:82%
Do you know the way home?

171
00:19:35.792 --> 00:19:38.833 line:82%
Yes, Dev. I know the way.
I just don't know you anymore.

172
00:19:40.292 --> 00:19:44.125 line:82%
It's strange. No one seems to have
a sense of humor this morning.

173
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.125 line:82%
Come on, let's go. Together.

174
00:19:56.708 --> 00:19:59.375 line:82%
-What is it?
-The house will collapse if you clean.

175
00:20:00.042 --> 00:20:00.917 line:82%
Rishi...

176
00:20:02.583 --> 00:20:04.417 line:82%
-What?
-Take off your pants.

177
00:20:05.083 --> 00:20:06.875 line:82%
-Take off what?
-Your pants.

178
00:20:07.417 --> 00:20:09.625 line:82%
-Here?
-Where, then?

179
00:20:14.417 --> 00:20:16.208 line:82%
Come on, Rishi. Quickly.
I don't have time.

180
00:20:16.292 --> 00:20:19.083 line:82%
I know. I've always wanted to do this
in the kitchen.

181
00:20:26.667 --> 00:20:28.083 line:82%
-Now it's your turn.
-Why?

182
00:20:28.875 --> 00:20:30.375 line:82%
Why? Then how are we?
It'll be kind of tough.

183
00:20:30.667 --> 00:20:32.958 line:82%
Rishi, I don't have to remove anything.

184
00:20:33.375 --> 00:20:35.750 line:82%
because my clothes have no stain.

185
00:20:35.958 --> 00:20:36.792 line:82%
Stain?

186
00:20:37.167 --> 00:20:40.708 line:82%
Yes. Stain. A big one.
And you were all set to go out with it.

187
00:20:42.583 --> 00:20:44.625 line:82%
When will you stop being
my mother and be my wife?

188
00:20:45.208 --> 00:20:47.958 line:82%
When you stop being my child
and become my husband.

189
00:20:50.167 --> 00:20:54.083 line:82%
If I stop being your child
who will you mother, then?

190
00:20:56.917 --> 00:20:57.750 line:82%
What happened?

191
00:20:58.083 --> 00:21:00.750 line:82%
Nothing.
Since I can't have children of my own.

192
00:21:01.083 --> 00:21:02.917 line:82%
I should think of you as my child, right?

193
00:21:03.417 --> 00:21:06.167 line:82%
Come on, Maya.
You know that's not what I meant.

194
00:21:06.250 --> 00:21:08.000 line:82%
-I really don't care about that.
-Here. Take this. It's gone.

195
00:21:11.792 --> 00:21:12.660 line:82%
listen.

196
00:21:13.414 --> 00:21:15.208 line:82%
Tonight's the Sanderson Hotel opening.

197
00:21:15.292 --> 00:21:16.792 line:82%
-What time do you want to go?
-I'm not coming.

198
00:21:19.042 --> 00:21:21.875 line:82%
If I go alone everywhere people
will think there's a problem.

199
00:21:22.542 --> 00:21:24.750 line:82%
-I don't care about people.
-And me?

200
00:21:28.167 --> 00:21:31.333 line:82%
Look, Rishi.
This night life, events, parties.

201
00:21:32.167 --> 00:21:33.708 line:82%
I don't belong to that part of your life.

202
00:21:35.417 --> 00:21:36.875 line:82%
Then which part of my life
do you belong to, Maya?

203
00:21:37.208 --> 00:21:38.708 line:82%
Which part of my life
do you belong to, Rishi?

204
00:21:39.167 --> 00:21:42.625 line:82%
When was the last time we did
something that I wanted?

205
00:21:43.375 --> 00:21:44.958 line:82%
You want to clean the house.

206
00:21:56.958 --> 00:22:00.667 line:82%
This is great! You start something
and then don't want to pursue it.

207
00:22:01.125 --> 00:22:02.208 line:82%
Rishi, I want to discuss.

208
00:22:28.625 --> 00:22:31.875 line:82%
Diva is America's No.2 fashion magazine.
Thanks to you.

209
00:22:56.542 --> 00:22:59.583 line:82%
I just spoke to the London head office
and we think you should move there.

210
00:23:00.917 --> 00:23:04.375 line:82%
Yeah. So that you can control
all the fashion magazines in the group.

211
00:23:09.083 --> 00:23:10.792 line:82%
This will be the biggest move
of your career.

212
00:23:11.875 --> 00:23:14.708 line:82%
No, Jai. This will be a big move
for your company.

213
00:23:18.792 --> 00:23:21.458 line:82%
You are intelligent,
confident, beautiful.

214
00:23:21.875 --> 00:23:24.958 line:82%
Just one problem. You are married.

215
00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:30.375 line:82%
But anyway married or unmarried.
How does it matter these days.

216
00:23:31.625 --> 00:23:32.792 line:82%
It matters to me, Jai.

217
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:40.833 line:82%
When I have said that we are not
organizing the party, why is he here?

218
00:23:42.083 --> 00:23:45.167 line:82%
He refuses to leave.
He says he won't go till we agree.

219
00:23:45.250 --> 00:23:47.125 line:82%
-What do you mean he won't leave?
-He's even threatening to sue us.

220
00:23:47.250 --> 00:23:48.542 line:82%
Sue. Who is he to?

221
00:23:48.792 --> 00:23:49.708 line:82%
I'll see to it.

222
00:23:58.792 --> 00:24:01.875 line:82%
But why?
You organize parties for the whole world.

223
00:24:01.958 --> 00:24:02.917 line:82%
Why can't you do it for your father?

224
00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:04.708 line:82%
The whole world hasn't had
two heart attacks.

225
00:24:05.333 --> 00:24:06.750 line:82%
Give some thought to your age.

226
00:24:07.125 --> 00:24:09.083 line:82%
What's age?
Just look at my heart.

227
00:24:09.417 --> 00:24:11.417 line:82%
Ask the beauties around,
they think I'm a rock star.

228
00:24:15.042 --> 00:24:17.917 line:82%
Hey, listen.
Why are you being so difficult?

229
00:24:18.042 --> 00:24:20.583 line:82%
It's just a simple party to be organized.
Here, listen to me.

230
00:24:20.958 --> 00:24:22.816 line:82%
Just give me a sixties setting,

231
00:24:22.900 --> 00:24:26.250 line:82%
the best wine
and a hundred beautiful girls. That's all.

232
00:24:28.375 --> 00:24:30.083 line:82%
And what do you plan to do
with hundred girls?

233
00:24:34.958 --> 00:24:38.167 line:82%
I want to know.
Why do you throw this party every year?

234
00:24:40.542 --> 00:24:41.375 line:82%
listen now.

235
00:24:41.458 --> 00:24:45.208 line:82%
Just organize this party
and my red Ferrari is yours.

236
00:24:48.417 --> 00:24:52.000 line:82%
If you think you can
buy me out by bribing me.

237
00:26:29.292 --> 00:26:30.625 line:82%
Where are you going, idiot?
Go...

238
00:26:50.792 --> 00:26:55.500 line:82%
Hit, Arjun. Hit.

239
00:27:37.708 --> 00:27:40.750 line:82%
I don't want to play football.
I want to play the violin.

240
00:27:40.833 --> 00:27:42.583 line:82%
What? You want to play the violin?

241
00:27:43.208 --> 00:27:44.750 line:82%
Wear a dress from tomorrow.

242
00:27:44.833 --> 00:27:46.875 line:82%
You will look perfect. Don't do that.
Just shut up.

243
00:27:50.792 --> 00:27:52.083 line:82%
Your son has lost the match again.

244
00:27:52.708 --> 00:27:53.833 line:82%
Looks like he's taken after his father.

245
00:27:56.167 --> 00:27:57.667 line:82%
Stop taking your anger out on him.

246
00:27:58.208 --> 00:28:00.000 line:82%
He'd probably have won
if you coached him well.

247
00:28:00.375 --> 00:28:03.542 line:82%
We'd probably have won
if you were here to boost our morale.

248
00:28:07.917 --> 00:28:10.542 line:82%
It's the Queen Mother for you.
Come on. Come on.

249
00:28:11.042 --> 00:28:14.958 line:82%
Mama, you have to be there for the
next match. You never come.

250
00:28:16.417 --> 00:28:17.667 line:82%
Next time I'll be there for sure.

251
00:28:18.042 --> 00:28:20.667 line:82%
Guess what?
Mama's got you a new PlayStation.

252
00:28:26.292 --> 00:28:29.042 line:82%
If they are selling some time
at the toy shop please buy that.

253
00:28:29.375 --> 00:28:30.583 line:82%
Arjun needs that a little more.

254
00:28:34.833 --> 00:28:36.542 line:82%
Tansen, I'm going to buy the tickets.

255
00:28:36.958 --> 00:28:39.292 line:82%
If you move from here,
I will slap you.

256
00:28:39.792 --> 00:28:41.417 line:82%
Let's go home
and I'll make you wear a dress.

257
00:28:45.375 --> 00:28:47.083 line:82%
OK, Tanya. Now listen to me.
Stay close to me all the time.

258
00:28:47.375 --> 00:28:49.542 line:82%
I read about the Black Beast this morning.

259
00:28:49.958 --> 00:28:51.917 line:82%
We never know where he might
be lurking in his black coat.

260
00:28:52.167 --> 00:28:54.125 line:82%
Now hold my hand. Is it clean?

261
00:28:55.875 --> 00:28:59.458 line:82%
Should we go here?
Or there? Who should I ask?

262
00:29:08.667 --> 00:29:14.667 line:82%
I saw you my beloved.

263
00:29:17.458 --> 00:29:22.917 line:82%
And it dawned on me how crazy love can be.

264
00:29:25.292 --> 00:29:26.125 line:82%
Me?

265
00:29:26.208 --> 00:29:29.750 line:82%
I saw you my beloved.

266
00:29:29.917 --> 00:29:31.917 line:82%
Here I come, Simran. Here I come.

267
00:29:50.000 --> 00:29:52.125 line:82%
Black Beast. When will they nab him?

268
00:29:57.792 --> 00:30:01.125 line:82%
Got you. I told you
not to move from there?

269
00:30:01.625 --> 00:30:02.458 line:82%
Then why did you move?

270
00:30:03.542 --> 00:30:07.250 line:82%
You kids have really troubled me today.
Specially you.

271
00:30:08.542 --> 00:30:09.917 line:82%
You know what I am going to do to you?

272
00:30:10.375 --> 00:30:13.458 line:82%
I'm going to cut you into tiny pieces

273
00:30:13.958 --> 00:30:16.792 line:82%
and put them in a mixer
to make Jamba juice.

274
00:30:24.083 --> 00:30:25.833 line:82%
Are we going to stand here all day?

275
00:30:26.083 --> 00:30:26.958 line:82%
Come with me now.

276
00:30:35.292 --> 00:30:36.958 line:82%
I don't know why children are born at all.

277
00:30:37.333 --> 00:30:38.875 line:82%
Why can't humans be born full grown?

278
00:30:44.333 --> 00:30:47.458 line:82%
I'm taking you to your Papa.
I won't let anything happen to you.

279
00:30:49.667 --> 00:30:51.542 line:82%
The next time you lose, I'm going to...

280
00:31:15.292 --> 00:31:19.167 line:82%
Give me a minute here. Come now. Run!

281
00:31:24.583 --> 00:31:26.500 line:82%
My ball!

282
00:31:26.600 --> 00:31:28.280 line:82%
-Shut up!
-Shut up!

283
00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:10.500 line:82%
She's become the Black Beast?

284
00:32:13.708 --> 00:32:14.958 line:82%
But why are you crying?

285
00:32:15.125 --> 00:32:16.625 line:82%
I thought I was being kidnapped.

286
00:32:16.792 --> 00:32:18.542 line:82%
I don't have such good fortune that
someone will kidnap you.

287
00:32:41.750 --> 00:32:43.000 line:82%
NYC
EMS AMBULANCE

288
00:33:10.167 --> 00:33:11.292 line:82%
Arjun, tell the fatso...

289
00:33:40.208 --> 00:33:42.167 line:82%
all this is my husband's fault.

290
00:33:42.250 --> 00:33:43.583 line:82%
Your husband is the Black Beast?

291
00:33:43.792 --> 00:33:46.000 line:82%
No, he's just a beast.

292
00:33:51.542 --> 00:33:53.083 line:82%
Your wife is fine now.

293
00:33:57.708 --> 00:33:58.625 line:82%
Rishi Talwar.

294
00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:00.958 line:82%
Rhea Saran.

295
00:34:08.958 --> 00:34:12.125 line:82%
I run a small PR firm named Kamakaze.

296
00:34:12.333 --> 00:34:14.708 line:82%
I've been trying to meet you for a while.

297
00:34:14.792 --> 00:34:16.542 line:82%
It's not easy meeting me.

298
00:34:16.625 --> 00:34:18.625 line:82%
Trust me, it's even more difficult
to avoid.

299
00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:51.500 line:82%
My lawyer will speak with you.

300
00:34:51.583 --> 00:34:53.167 line:82%
And my lawyer will speak to you.

301
00:34:57.000 --> 00:35:00.333 line:82%
You. I know you.

302
00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:04.083 line:82%
Even I remember. We've met before.

303
00:35:06.920 --> 00:35:09.625 line:82%
Now I can't walk for a week
because of you.

304
00:35:11.042 --> 00:35:12.958 line:82%
I can't walk for life because of you.

305
00:35:14.417 --> 00:35:15.292 line:82%
What?

306
00:35:16.333 --> 00:35:19.167 line:82%
If I hadn't met you, my life
would have been different.

307
00:35:19.292 --> 00:35:21.625 line:82%
My pain would have been different.

308
00:35:22.208 --> 00:35:24.125 line:82%
And if I hadn't met you
I wouldn't have married...

309
00:35:24.208 --> 00:35:25.833 line:82%
Wouldn't have married?

310
00:35:30.208 --> 00:35:32.125 line:82%
ls that a good thing or a bad thing?

311
00:35:32.250 --> 00:35:33.083 line:82%
-Good.
-Good?

312
00:35:33.167 --> 00:35:34.583 line:82%
-Bad.
-Bad?

313
00:35:41.458 --> 00:35:42.458 line:82%
Are you happy?

314
00:35:46.833 --> 00:35:49.417 line:82%
-You can't take that long.
-Who are you to ask me all this?

315
00:35:49.625 --> 00:35:51.458 line:82%
You can't answer a question
with a question.

316
00:35:51.833 --> 00:35:52.917 line:82%
Why should I bother about your questions?

317
00:35:53.167 --> 00:35:55.083 line:82%
Why should I answer you? Who are you?

318
00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:00.458 line:82%
I'm the father of the child you were
running away with.

319
00:36:01.208 --> 00:36:03.750 line:82%
Don't you have your own children?

320
00:36:09.625 --> 00:36:10.458 line:82%
You don't.

321
00:36:11.083 --> 00:36:13.208 line:82%
Yes. I don't have any.
I can't have them.

322
00:36:13.750 --> 00:36:16.292 line:82%
I teach children.
I'm a mother to all of them.

323
00:36:16.583 --> 00:36:18.042 line:82%
Mother India.

324
00:36:18.833 --> 00:36:22.380 line:82%
Teaching children.
Running away with them,

325
00:36:22.458 --> 00:36:23.940 line:82%
Are you able to fill
your emptiness with it?

326
00:36:24.208 --> 00:36:27.458 line:82%
Because your life is empty. Incomplete.

327
00:36:28.792 --> 00:36:30.700 line:82%
It shows in your eyes.

328
00:36:33.792 --> 00:36:35.208 line:82%
Just like in mine.

329
00:36:41.625 --> 00:36:42.708 line:82%
Why did you take the trouble?

330
00:36:42.792 --> 00:36:44.250 line:82%
You are so considerate.

331
00:36:44.542 --> 00:36:47.000 line:82%
I'm beginning to feel pressurized
by your niceness.

332
00:37:05.208 --> 00:37:06.292 line:82%
Rishi Kapoor?

333
00:37:15.917 --> 00:37:16.750 line:82%
Goodbye.

334
00:37:18.875 --> 00:37:19.708 line:82%
No good bye.

335
00:37:20.667 --> 00:37:23.667 line:82%
Goodbye kills all hope of meeting again.

336
00:37:24.667 --> 00:37:27.708 line:82%
And who knows?
We might meet again.

337
00:37:33.875 --> 00:37:36.083 line:82%
Dev, no one ever wants to meet you again.

338
00:37:49.917 --> 00:37:52.667 line:82%
The doctor has said you'll
be fine in two to three days.

339
00:37:52.759 --> 00:37:54.079 line:82%
After that...

340
00:38:02.833 --> 00:38:06.250 line:82%
God. Not you. It's that...
What was his name?

341
00:38:06.583 --> 00:38:08.333 line:82%
Dev, he was talking nonsense

342
00:38:08.667 --> 00:38:10.542 line:82%
and did you see how
he was talking to his wife?

343
00:38:13.375 --> 00:38:17.083 line:82%
Maya, not all husbands
can be as good as me.

344
00:38:19.208 --> 00:38:22.458 line:82%
To keep my heart at your feet.

345
00:38:58.625 --> 00:38:59.583 line:82%
You?

346
00:38:59.667 --> 00:39:02.458 line:82%
Of course not. It's someone else.
What a strange question.

347
00:39:02.542 --> 00:39:03.958 line:82%
You? Who else will I be?

348
00:39:04.167 --> 00:39:06.399 line:82%
-Whatever... I'm glad you are here.
-Were you thinking of me?

349
00:39:06.708 --> 00:39:09.019 line:82%
Yes... I've been thinking
of you for a week.

350
00:39:09.250 --> 00:39:11.699 line:82%
listen all that I said that day
was because of the injection.

351
00:39:11.919 --> 00:39:15.500 line:82%
I'm married. And to think of a married man
in that way is a sin.

352
00:39:15.583 --> 00:39:17.000 line:82%
-You talk rubbish.
-Yeah.

353
00:39:17.167 --> 00:39:19.750 line:82%
I wanted to meet you to say that
the things you said to me that day--

354
00:39:19.833 --> 00:39:21.917 line:82%
Was true...
And the truth is always bitter.

355
00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:24.583 line:82%
You are bitter. Not the truth.
And who are you?

356
00:39:24.667 --> 00:39:27.625 line:82%
The Supreme court?
To pass judgments on others lives?

357
00:39:32.083 --> 00:39:34.125 line:82%
listen. I'm very happy.
Thank you.

358
00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:36.083 line:82%
You should think about your own life.

359
00:39:36.375 --> 00:39:39.792 line:82%
I'm sure your life is empty
and your dreams, unfulfilled.

360
00:39:39.875 --> 00:39:41.917 line:82%
That's why you keep searching
for the same in others lives.

361
00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:53.583 line:82%
Maya... Maya, just listen.

362
00:39:53.667 --> 00:39:56.917 line:82%
We are both alike, very alike.
I'm sorry.

363
00:39:57.958 --> 00:40:00.583 line:82%
We travel from the same station.
Both teach children.

364
00:40:01.458 --> 00:40:02.542 line:82%
Both of us are wounded.

365
00:40:02.625 --> 00:40:06.542 line:82%
It's just that my wounds show,
yours don't.

366
00:40:12.042 --> 00:40:15.958 line:82%
And can we discuss our sad lives
over coffee?

367
00:40:16.208 --> 00:40:19.000 line:82%
No, thank you.
My husband's waiting for me at home.

368
00:40:21.250 --> 00:40:23.750 line:82%
Well, even Rhea must be home by now.

369
00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:55.917 line:82%
Dude, what's going on here?

370
00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:57.208 line:82%
What went on is over now.

371
00:41:03.042 --> 00:41:05.833 line:82%
We were just passing by
and so we thought we'd just...

372
00:41:12.708 --> 00:41:14.125 line:82%
If Maya arrives now she will kill me.

373
00:41:14.333 --> 00:41:15.500 line:82%
Papa is going to kill me.

374
00:41:15.667 --> 00:41:17.917 line:82%
Today was the music class
so I bunked football.

375
00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:20.375 line:82%
No, my child. Nothing will happen.
I'll take care of it.

376
00:41:20.458 --> 00:41:21.917 line:82%
No, grandma he's going to kill me.

377
00:41:22.000 --> 00:41:23.125 line:82%
Why will he kill you?

378
00:41:23.208 --> 00:41:24.875 line:82%
You are learning the guitar
and that's a good thing.

379
00:41:24.958 --> 00:41:26.500 line:82%
Not guitar, Mom.
violin.

380
00:41:26.708 --> 00:41:29.958 line:82%
violin... I don't understand
why he is so scared of Dev...

381
00:41:30.042 --> 00:41:32.125 line:82%
-But Mom, you don't understand.
-No, darling you relax.

382
00:41:32.208 --> 00:41:33.042 line:82%
But Mom.

383
00:41:33.875 --> 00:41:35.708 line:82%
Shut up! Nothing's going to happen.

384
00:41:35.917 --> 00:41:38.500 line:82%
I'll tell Dev that you are not well. OK?

385
00:41:39.500 --> 00:41:41.125 line:82%
Why should we lie?

386
00:41:42.625 --> 00:41:46.708 line:82%
Now come on go upstairs and grandma will
give you a nice hot water bath.

387
00:41:49.083 --> 00:41:51.750 line:82%
Shit. Maya has come.
Please hide this one somewhere?

388
00:41:51.833 --> 00:41:53.250 line:82%
In my arms?

389
00:42:04.458 --> 00:42:06.042 line:82%
-Son, do you know--
-I know.

390
00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:09.833 line:82%
I know everything.

391
00:42:10.333 --> 00:42:11.917 line:82%
Everything? No. I think you.

392
00:42:15.917 --> 00:42:21.083 line:82%
Don't try to hide
from me I know everything.

393
00:42:21.458 --> 00:42:24.167 line:82%
Yes, I know. I saw it with my eyes.

394
00:42:25.292 --> 00:42:26.417 line:82%
Did you hear that? She knows everything.

395
00:42:26.542 --> 00:42:28.375 line:82%
Look at this.
And we were trying to hide from her.

396
00:42:28.875 --> 00:42:31.083 line:82%
Dad! Even you know?

397
00:42:31.333 --> 00:42:34.583 line:82%
What do you mean when did I know?
It was my idea to make an excuse.

398
00:42:34.667 --> 00:42:36.375 line:82%
Now the poor fellow is hiding
in the bathroom.

399
00:42:37.667 --> 00:42:38.667 line:82%
He's in my bathroom?

400
00:42:38.875 --> 00:42:40.083 line:82%
She is in my bedroom?

401
00:42:40.875 --> 00:42:43.667 line:82%
Don't go in.
Poor thing, she's not wearing anything.

402
00:42:44.125 --> 00:42:45.500 line:82%
What is she doing without clothes?

403
00:42:51.792 --> 00:42:52.958 line:82%
What do you do without clothes?

404
00:42:54.583 --> 00:42:58.667 line:82%
-I will not let him live. I'm going to--
-What are you doing?

405
00:43:00.375 --> 00:43:03.859 line:82%
I am begging. He's already too scared.
I'm going to him now.

406
00:43:04.019 --> 00:43:05.879 line:82%
-Why?
-To give him a bath.

407
00:43:05.958 --> 00:43:09.250 line:82%
So now you will bathe him?
That too in my bathroom.

408
00:43:09.458 --> 00:43:10.799 line:82%
The bathroom doesn't belong to just you.

409
00:43:10.959 --> 00:43:14.500 line:82%
It's mine, too. He will use it...
Both of us will bathe him.

410
00:43:16.625 --> 00:43:18.208 line:82%
How could you do this?
Aren't you ashamed?

411
00:43:18.292 --> 00:43:19.542 line:82%
But what have I done?

412
00:43:19.625 --> 00:43:21.625 line:82%
Please. Please! You two stop fighting.

413
00:43:21.708 --> 00:43:22.708 line:82%
I'm taking her to my house.

414
00:43:22.792 --> 00:43:24.167 line:82%
Why would you take her to your house?

415
00:43:24.417 --> 00:43:26.708 line:82%
-Because I paid her.
-She takes money?

416
00:43:26.792 --> 00:43:28.542 line:82%
Yeah. Nothing comes for free these days.

417
00:43:28.917 --> 00:43:30.375 line:82%
By the way what's the rate these days?

418
00:43:30.583 --> 00:43:32.958 line:82%
-Per day or weekends?
-Weekends.

419
00:43:35.542 --> 00:43:37.042 line:82%
Both of you have gone crazy.

420
00:43:37.250 --> 00:43:38.625 line:82%
No, Dev. You are crazy.

421
00:43:38.708 --> 00:43:39.833 line:82%
Look at what you are doing.

422
00:43:39.958 --> 00:43:41.875 line:82%
I can't take this anymore.
I'm sleeping with him tonight.

423
00:43:41.958 --> 00:43:43.125 line:82%
-Me, too.
-You, too?

424
00:43:43.208 --> 00:43:45.417 line:82%
Have some shame.
Look at his age and yours.

425
00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:46.542 line:82%
You look at your age.

426
00:43:46.625 --> 00:43:47.542 line:82%
Don't cross your limits.

427
00:43:49.125 --> 00:43:50.708 line:82%
What about your limits?

428
00:43:50.875 --> 00:43:53.792 line:82%
The two of you... both...

429
00:43:57.399 --> 00:44:01.125 line:82%
And she. I will not spare her. Rhea!

430
00:44:16.792 --> 00:44:18.990 line:82%
He was just inviting me
for his Dad's party

431
00:44:19.074 --> 00:44:20.458 line:82%
so that I can see his work.

432
00:44:20.833 --> 00:44:22.417 line:82%
It's just a PR exercise, Dev.

433
00:44:22.500 --> 00:44:23.333 line:82%
What about the flowers?

434
00:44:23.417 --> 00:44:25.125 line:82%
Rhea sent them for you.

435
00:44:30.167 --> 00:44:31.292 line:82%
And who is this?

436
00:44:31.542 --> 00:44:34.333 line:82%
This? This is your mother to be.

437
00:44:40.208 --> 00:44:42.083 line:82%
You thought I was having
an affair with Rishi?

438
00:44:42.417 --> 00:44:45.333 line:82%
What's with you, Dev?
