01:25:21.333 --> 01:25:24.333 line:82%
I'm a failure. That's true.

900
01:25:27.250 --> 01:25:31.292 line:82%
But do you know, there's a greater
failure than me in this house?

901
01:25:34.500 --> 01:25:35.459 line:82%
Our relationship.

902
01:25:40.208 --> 01:25:41.500 line:82%
Our marriage.

903
01:26:51.667 --> 01:26:53.125 line:82%
Why are you so angry, Rishi?

904
01:26:53.958 --> 01:26:56.000 line:82%
What's the big deal
if I didn't feel like it one night?

905
01:26:56.292 --> 01:26:57.625 line:82%
Come on, don't behave like a child.

906
01:27:02.208 --> 01:27:03.625 line:82%
I have heard enough.

907
01:27:06.417 --> 01:27:11.667 line:82%
Maya, do you remember the last time
we were intimate with each other?

908
01:27:12.458 --> 01:27:17.000 line:82%
When, Maya?
When did we touch each other?

909
01:27:17.250 --> 01:27:19.792 line:82%
Held hands or embraced? Anything?
Do you remember?

910
01:27:21.208 --> 01:27:23.917 line:82%
When did we not turn our backs to each
other in bed? Do you remember?

911
01:27:25.375 --> 01:27:26.417 line:82%
I don't remember...

912
01:27:26.833 --> 01:27:28.250 line:82%
You don't remember
or don't want to remember.

913
01:27:29.625 --> 01:27:32.792 line:82%
Why? I thought you like discussions.

914
01:27:39.917 --> 01:27:42.625 line:82%
Our relationship cannot grow just
by sleeping with each other, Rishi.

915
01:27:43.083 --> 01:27:46.042 line:82%
It can only grow when we embrace
each other's sorrow and happiness.

916
01:27:46.500 --> 01:27:49.167 line:82%
And when was the last time
we did that? When, Rishi?

917
01:27:50.083 --> 01:27:53.208 line:82%
A husband and wife don't just share a bed.
They share their lives.

918
01:27:57.667 --> 01:28:00.917 line:82%
Do you think I'm the kind of man who only
feels the need for his wife in his bed?

919
01:28:02.500 --> 01:28:05.875 line:82%
To embrace each other's happiness and pain
one has to embrace each other.

920
01:28:06.542 --> 01:28:08.625 line:82%
And you have never felt that way about me.

921
01:28:09.208 --> 01:28:10.417 line:82%
'You are a child, you are a child,
you are a child'

922
01:28:10.500 --> 01:28:11.792 line:82%
I'm fed up of hearing that.

923
01:28:12.250 --> 01:28:15.625 line:82%
If I was truly a child,
I'd have broken down long ago.

924
01:28:16.208 --> 01:28:17.958 line:82%
I tolerate you because I'm a man.

925
01:28:23.500 --> 01:28:25.625 line:82%
Today you cannot leave like this.

926
01:28:26.125 --> 01:28:27.667 line:82%
You will have to tell me today.

927
01:28:27.750 --> 01:28:31.833 line:82%
The truth.
Tell me, why did you marry me?

928
01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:37.875 line:82%
Why?
I married you because I love you.

929
01:28:39.792 --> 01:28:44.458 line:82%
I love you very much.
But why did you marry me, Maya?

930
01:28:46.792 --> 01:28:49.917 line:82%
Tell me. Why did you marry me?

931
01:29:03.958 --> 01:29:09.125 line:82%
The truth, Maya,
is that you never married me.

932
01:29:11.083 --> 01:29:12.399 line:82%
You compromised.

933
01:29:16.667 --> 01:29:19.250 line:82%
I'm your life's biggest compromise.

934
01:29:22.917 --> 01:29:26.708 line:82%
A compromise that you regret
every day of your life, right?

935
01:29:29.792 --> 01:29:32.500 line:82%
That's the truth, right?

936
01:29:34.779 --> 01:29:35.719 line:82%
Give me an answer.

937
01:29:38.708 --> 01:29:39.739 line:82%
What answer?

938
01:29:41.875 --> 01:29:46.458 line:82%
You have nothing to give.
Nothing at all.

939
01:29:47.458 --> 01:29:49.958 line:82%
Not love, not happiness,
not affection.

940
01:29:50.042 --> 01:29:51.875 line:82%
You haven't even been able
to give me a child.

941
01:29:55.750 --> 01:29:59.833 line:82%
And Maya, I have never made you feel
inadequate about that. Never.

942
01:30:12.458 --> 01:30:13.458 line:82%
You just did.

943
01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:18.219 line:82%
Just did it, Rishi.

944
01:31:10.125 --> 01:31:13.333 line:82%
Four years ago, you said that everlasting
romances don't exist anymore.

945
01:31:13.625 --> 01:31:14.542 line:82%
Remember, Dev?

946
01:31:15.417 --> 01:31:16.750 line:82%
Will you say the same even now?

947
01:31:17.583 --> 01:31:19.208 line:82%
Four years ago, you said that

948
01:31:19.917 --> 01:31:22.375 line:82%
if I don't look for love after marriage,
I won't find it

949
01:31:23.292 --> 01:31:24.333 line:82%
What will you say now, Dev?

950
01:31:24.875 --> 01:31:25.958 line:82%
What will you say?

951
01:31:26.167 --> 01:31:27.125 line:82%
Answer me...

952
01:31:27.417 --> 01:31:29.833 line:82%
What are you and me doing at the station
in the middle of the night?

953
01:31:30.708 --> 01:31:31.583 line:82%
What are we doing, Dev?

954
01:31:31.833 --> 01:31:33.833 line:82%
Answer me.
I need answers to all these questions.

955
01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:35.958 line:82%
Where are you going, Dev?

956
01:31:37.875 --> 01:31:39.375 line:82%
Answer me!
Answer me, Dev!

957
01:31:40.958 --> 01:31:46.750 line:82%
18th March 2002.
You met me for the first time, Maya.

958
01:31:49.042 --> 01:31:51.500 line:82%
Since that day I have felt like
I have known you forever.

959
01:31:51.583 --> 01:31:53.167 line:82%
ls this the answer to your question?

960
01:31:56.083 --> 01:31:59.083 line:82%
Everyday your train leaves the station
at 4:32.

961
01:31:59.208 --> 01:32:03.125 line:82%
and mine at 4:21.
Everyday I miss my train

962
01:32:03.708 --> 01:32:06.333 line:82%
so that I can spend some more moments
with you.

963
01:32:06.458 --> 01:32:07.875 line:82%
Is this the answer to your question?

964
01:32:08.833 --> 01:32:12.708 line:82%
Everyday I leave you at the station but
your thoughts don't leave me.

965
01:32:14.417 --> 01:32:16.042 line:82%
ls this the answer to your question?

966
01:32:17.917 --> 01:32:20.000 line:82%
Maybe you've forgotten that you are, too.

967
01:32:20.750 --> 01:32:21.875 line:82%
Since both of us are married,

968
01:32:21.958 --> 01:32:24.958 line:82%
what are we doing at the station
in the middle of the night?

969
01:32:29.625 --> 01:32:32.542 line:82%
That's the answer to your question, right?
listen to the answer.

970
01:33:09.833 --> 01:33:11.500 line:82%
You are Dev's mother,
you will take his side.

971
01:33:11.583 --> 01:33:13.583 line:82%
I'm a woman before I'm a mother, Rhea.

972
01:33:13.958 --> 01:33:18.458 line:82%
And I know you are right. Nothing will
happen just because I think it is.

973
01:33:18.833 --> 01:33:20.208 line:82%
The situation is not going to change.

974
01:33:20.667 --> 01:33:22.708 line:82%
Things will only change when Dev changes.

975
01:33:26.042 --> 01:33:28.417 line:82%
Mom, please I'm tired.

976
01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:32.083 line:82%
I've tried enough to understand him,
to get closer to him.

977
01:33:32.667 --> 01:33:36.833 line:82%
One fine day, he just decided to step back
from the relationship.

978
01:33:37.167 --> 01:33:41.250 line:82%
He did not step back, Rhea.
You raced ahead.

979
01:33:41.917 --> 01:33:43.458 line:82%
You have to wait for him.

980
01:33:43.792 --> 01:33:46.958 line:82%
Why? Why is a woman always expected
to wait.

981
01:33:47.625 --> 01:33:53.125 line:82%
Because they are stronger.
And have you thought about Arjun?

982
01:33:53.417 --> 01:33:55.292 line:82%
I'm not the kind of woman,

983
01:33:55.417 --> 01:33:57.500 line:82%
who will use her child
as an excuse to back down.

984
01:33:57.708 --> 01:33:59.208 line:82%
I'm not that weak.

985
01:33:59.542 --> 01:34:02.792 line:82%
You are not weak.
Your relationship is.

986
01:34:03.042 --> 01:34:05.583 line:82%
You have to give it strength.
You have to give it time.

987
01:34:05.917 --> 01:34:10.542 line:82%
I will give this relationship nothing,
till Dev gives it love.

988
01:34:16.750 --> 01:34:18.042 line:82%
You are going somewhere?

989
01:34:19.167 --> 01:34:23.542 line:82%
Paris. For ten days.
To organize a few events.

990
01:34:24.792 --> 01:34:26.250 line:82%
Last night the things you said to her--

991
01:34:26.333 --> 01:34:29.000 line:82%
Last night I said a lot of things
I shouldn't have,

992
01:34:29.875 --> 01:34:33.042 line:82%
and a few that were very important to say.

993
01:34:34.958 --> 01:34:36.250 line:82%
Try to understand her, Rishi.

994
01:34:39.458 --> 01:34:43.000 line:82%
How do I understand a heart that
has no place for me?

995
01:34:44.250 --> 01:34:48.042 line:82%
That's not true, Rishi.
She loves you a lot.

996
01:34:49.250 --> 01:34:54.875 line:82%
Look into her eyes.
Who else can all that love be for?

997
01:34:55.083 --> 01:34:58.917 line:82%
I wish the love in her eyes reached
her lips once in a while.

998
01:34:59.292 --> 01:35:03.458 line:82%
Dad, everyday I tell her how much
I love her, has she ever said it?

999
01:35:06.917 --> 01:35:09.208 line:82%
Sorry, dad. I can't take it.

1000
01:35:13.419 --> 01:35:14.500 line:82%
Not anymore.

1001
01:35:32.125 --> 01:35:32.958 line:82%
Now?

1002
01:35:36.542 --> 01:35:37.583 line:82%
Now what, Dev?

1003
01:35:42.000 --> 01:35:46.375 line:82%
It was important to say
that we love each other.

1004
01:35:47.542 --> 01:35:48.750 line:82%
So, we've said it.

1005
01:35:49.500 --> 01:35:51.125 line:82%
And what did we gain by saying it?

1006
01:35:52.625 --> 01:35:53.779 line:82%
I don't know.

1007
01:35:56.125 --> 01:36:00.542 line:82%
But if we hadn't,
we would have lost something.

1008
01:36:05.167 --> 01:36:09.208 line:82%
You know Dev, that this
relationship has no future.

1009
01:36:15.083 --> 01:36:20.083 line:82%
That's why it needs to be abandoned
on this beautiful note.

1010
01:36:43.125 --> 01:36:44.250 line:82%
Your train.

1011
01:36:48.083 --> 01:36:49.375 line:82%
Not my train anymore.

1012
01:36:51.542 --> 01:36:54.875 line:82%
I'm planning to stop traveling by train.

1013
01:38:08.333 --> 01:38:12.542 line:82%
Your life is empty.
I can see it in your eyes.

1014
01:38:14.667 --> 01:38:16.958 line:82%
Do you remember
when we touched each other?

1015
01:38:17.250 --> 01:38:19.583 line:82%
Held hands? Anything? Do you remember?

1016
01:38:20.208 --> 01:38:24.417 line:82%
I leave you at the station everyday
but your thoughts never leave me.

1017
01:38:24.750 --> 01:38:28.167 line:82%
To embrace each other's happiness
and pain, one has to embrace each other.

1018
01:38:28.333 --> 01:38:30.167 line:82%
And you have never felt
that way about me.

1019
01:38:30.333 --> 01:38:31.458 line:82%
Since both of us are married

1020
01:38:31.542 --> 01:38:34.833 line:82%
what are we doing at the station
in the middle of the night?

1021
01:38:35.167 --> 01:38:40.167 line:82%
You have to tell me today, Maya.
Tell me the truth, why did you marry me?

1022
01:38:40.250 --> 01:38:41.625 line:82%
Why?

1023
01:38:42.125 --> 01:38:44.667 line:82%
Sometimes friendship takes
the place of love.

1024
01:38:45.458 --> 01:38:47.542 line:82%
and then there's no place left for love.

1025
01:38:49.000 --> 01:38:53.542 line:82%
The truth is, that you never married me,

1026
01:38:55.000 --> 01:38:56.542 line:82%
You compromised.

1027
01:38:56.750 --> 01:38:58.375 line:82%
Listen to the answer, Maya.

1028
01:39:08.625 --> 01:39:11.917 line:82%
And what if I find my soul mate
after marriage?

1029
01:39:39.333 --> 01:39:40.417 line:82%
Dev!

1030
01:40:36.750 --> 01:40:41.833 line:82%
Do you know when we reached here?

1031
01:40:43.458 --> 01:40:48.250 line:82%
I am yours and you mine

1032
01:40:48.583 --> 01:40:54.500 line:82%
I'm wonder struck at this moment.
What can I say to you?

1033
01:40:55.292 --> 01:41:00.208 line:82%
When moonlight has emerged in
the middle of the day

1034
01:41:00.667 --> 01:41:06.458 line:82%
It seems awake yet it's dreaming

1035
01:41:07.542 --> 01:41:11.958 line:82%
My lovelorn life

1036
01:42:06.125 --> 01:42:11.750 line:82%
Intoxicated souls
Musky bodies

1037
01:42:12.208 --> 01:42:16.375 line:82%
There's a pureness in the air

1038
01:42:18.083 --> 01:42:23.625 line:82%
In this moment that we are in
there's so much color

1039
01:42:23.958 --> 01:42:29.375 line:82%
Spilling out of our eyes

1040
01:42:29.667 --> 01:42:35.667 line:82%
The blue sky showers on us

1041
01:42:36.417 --> 01:42:41.125 line:82%
Soft silky rays of light

1042
01:42:41.279 --> 01:42:47.179 line:82%
Do you know when we reached here?

1043
01:42:47.833 --> 01:42:52.833 line:82%
I am yours and you mine

1044
01:42:52.999 --> 01:42:58.599 line:82%
I'm wonder struck at this moment.
What can I say to you?

1045
01:42:59.799 --> 01:43:03.879 line:82%
When moonlight has emerged in
the middle of the day

1046
01:43:35.083 --> 01:43:40.792 line:82%
I was blissfully ignorant

1047
01:43:41.042 --> 01:43:45.875 line:82%
Of this love that flows forth unbridled

1048
01:43:47.167 --> 01:43:52.875 line:82%
True is this feeling
This feeling is called love

1049
01:43:52.958 --> 01:43:58.083 line:82%
All else is just an illusion

1050
01:43:58.708 --> 01:44:04.708 line:82%
My heart slowly hums

1051
01:44:05.167 --> 01:44:10.208 line:82%
The melodious notes of love

1052
01:44:10.292 --> 01:44:15.958 line:82%
Do you know when we reached here?

1053
01:44:16.750 --> 01:44:21.500 line:82%
I am yours and you mine

1054
01:44:21.917 --> 01:44:27.917 line:82%
I'm wonder struck at this moment
What can I say to you?

1055
01:44:28.625 --> 01:44:33.917 line:82%
When moonlight has emerged
in the middle of the day

1056
01:44:34.125 --> 01:44:40.125 line:82%
It seems awake yet it's dreaming

1057
01:44:40.875 --> 01:44:44.833 line:82%
My lovelorn life

1058
01:45:16.333 --> 01:45:19.999 line:82%
We were crazy. We were strange.
We were different.

1059
01:45:20.199 --> 01:45:24.708 line:82%
Very different. Incomplete on our own
but so complete together.

1060
01:45:25.583 --> 01:45:30.333 line:82%
We were not walking on the ground.
There, we had slipped long ago.

1061
01:45:30.708 --> 01:45:34.208 line:82%
We were flying in the sky.
Talking to the clouds.

1062
01:45:34.500 --> 01:45:38.875 line:82%
We didn't have a care in the world.
We had made our own world.

1063
01:45:39.125 --> 01:45:42.750 line:82%
Our world. Maya and Dev's world.

1064
01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:47.333 line:82%
The world of our dreams.

1065
01:45:55.708 --> 01:46:00.667 line:82%
But then dreams always leave
when you wake up to reality.

1066
01:46:02.875 --> 01:46:04.875 line:82%
Come on, drink your milk quickly.

1067
01:46:05.167 --> 01:46:07.208 line:82%
-I don't want to drink it.
-Drink it.

1068
01:46:17.458 --> 01:46:20.000 line:82%
I was going to ask you for advice
and I come to know.

1069
01:46:20.083 --> 01:46:22.583 line:82%
that it's the same situation
in your house, too.

1070
01:46:23.833 --> 01:46:25.625 line:82%
Every house seems to have the same story.

1071
01:46:26.708 --> 01:46:28.417 line:82%
Will you stop this TV soap commentary?

1072
01:46:32.250 --> 01:46:34.333 line:82%
Look, your son is mule headed.

1073
01:46:34.750 --> 01:46:35.917 line:82%
He is not going to do anything.

1074
01:46:36.458 --> 01:46:38.667 line:82%
Maya isn't at fault so she
isn't going to do anything.

1075
01:46:44.083 --> 01:46:46.917 line:82%
Whatever needs to be done
has to be done by Rhea and Rishi.

1076
01:46:50.083 --> 01:46:51.667 line:82%
Who will convince them?

1077
01:46:52.292 --> 01:46:53.917 line:82%
What if they convince each other?

1078
01:46:54.292 --> 01:46:56.042 line:82%
And why will they do that?

1079
01:46:59.500 --> 01:47:01.125 line:82%
Two strangers, same situation.

1080
01:47:01.333 --> 01:47:04.792 line:82%
Then, friendship and problem solved.
Remember?

1081
01:47:05.667 --> 01:47:08.000 line:82%
But how will they meet each other?

1082
01:47:10.167 --> 01:47:11.208 line:82%
Dad, what are we doing here?

1083
01:47:11.333 --> 01:47:13.125 line:82%
I haven't bought you a present
in a long time.

1084
01:47:13.208 --> 01:47:14.375 line:82%
So I thought I'd do that today.

1085
01:47:17.375 --> 01:47:18.708 line:82%
It's for kids.

1086
01:47:20.292 --> 01:47:23.208 line:82%
But to me you will always be a kid.

1087
01:47:23.375 --> 01:47:25.875 line:82%
Mom, should I take this for Arjun?

1088
01:47:26.167 --> 01:47:29.042 line:82%
Yes, take it. It's very nice.
It's fantastic.

1089
01:47:29.125 --> 01:47:31.458 line:82%
You have very good taste.
It's a fabulous dog, take it.

1090
01:47:36.583 --> 01:47:38.159 line:82%
OK, I'll take this.

1091
01:47:38.667 --> 01:47:41.417 line:82%
God! What an awful red dog.
Just leave it.

1092
01:47:47.792 --> 01:47:50.375 line:82%
Of all the places in New York
we had to meet here.

1093
01:47:55.417 --> 01:47:57.042 line:82%
By the way what are you doing here?

1094
01:47:57.208 --> 01:48:00.125 line:82%
We had come here to buy
a soft toy for my grandson

1095
01:48:00.375 --> 01:48:02.417 line:82%
which he can cuddle to at night.

1096
01:48:02.708 --> 01:48:07.375 line:82%
Even I was looking for something
like that. And I saw you.

1097
01:48:07.833 --> 01:48:12.375 line:82%
Neither am I soft nor am I a toy.
So please stay away.

1098
01:48:20.875 --> 01:48:25.542 line:82%
There are so many beautiful
things here. Red, blue, green...

1099
01:48:34.458 --> 01:48:36.167 line:82%
Don't you think that was weird behavior?

1100
01:48:45.458 --> 01:48:46.500 line:82%
Where are you heading?

1101
01:49:04.625 --> 01:49:06.458 line:82%
Why are people so happy in New York?

1102
01:49:06.708 --> 01:49:09.208 line:82%
Because they are not married. That's why.

1103
01:49:15.625 --> 01:49:17.125 line:82%
They go home, take a shower
and freshen themselves.

1104
01:49:17.333 --> 01:49:18.167 line:82%
Watch TV.

1105
01:49:21.542 --> 01:49:23.750 line:82%
True. We go home to a sour face.

1106
01:49:23.958 --> 01:49:26.083 line:82%
That likes nothing. That likes no one.

1107
01:49:26.167 --> 01:49:27.542 line:82%
Not even us.

1108
01:49:31.042 --> 01:49:33.292 line:82%
-But have they ever complimented us?
-Never!

1109
01:49:33.542 --> 01:49:35.333 line:82%
All the time whine, whine, whine.

1110
01:49:39.375 --> 01:49:40.417 line:82%
My God, how they trouble us.

1111
01:49:40.500 --> 01:49:41.333 line:82%
How they sadden us.

1112
01:49:41.417 --> 01:49:43.458 line:82%
-Mock us.
-Hurt us.

1113
01:49:43.667 --> 01:49:44.542 line:82%
Why did we marry?

1114
01:49:44.958 --> 01:49:47.250 line:82%
I know.
Our brains were not working.

1115
01:49:49.000 --> 01:49:52.000 line:82%
You know what? We should be single.

1116
01:50:06.708 --> 01:50:09.083 line:82%
-We are lying.
-What?

1117
01:50:16.792 --> 01:50:19.917 line:82%
You have called me five times
since morning. What's the problem?

1118
01:50:20.125 --> 01:50:22.083 line:82%
The problem is that
my work is that kind.

1119
01:50:22.875 --> 01:50:26.167 line:82%
I never have the time
to express my feeling.

1120
01:50:26.333 --> 01:50:28.417 line:82%
And I keep expressing
my feelings all the time.

1121
01:50:28.750 --> 01:50:30.417 line:82%
So what's stopping you today?

1122
01:50:34.458 --> 01:50:36.583 line:82%
Nothing's stopping you either.

1123
01:50:36.792 --> 01:50:38.167 line:82%
Do you like diamonds, Maya?

1124
01:50:39.375 --> 01:50:41.500 line:82%
Large, beautiful and expensive diamonds.

1125
01:50:43.958 --> 01:50:45.458 line:82%
Tell your husband to buy them for you.

1126
01:50:47.875 --> 01:50:49.750 line:82%
I have bought you flowers.

1127
01:50:54.792 --> 01:50:59.083 line:82%
OK, I'll call him if you speak to Maya.

1128
01:50:59.167 --> 01:51:02.125 line:82%
Why should I speak any longer?
I'm meeting you in five minutes.

1129
01:51:02.500 --> 01:51:04.458 line:82%
Then speak to me
for four and a half minute.

1130
01:51:16.167 --> 01:51:19.792 line:82%
Maya, I'm sulking
and you aren't even trying to make up.

1131
01:51:23.792 --> 01:51:27.500 line:82%
Say or do something which
shows that you are mine.

1132
01:51:28.292 --> 01:51:29.458 line:82%
Only mine.

1133
01:51:38.542 --> 01:51:39.625 line:82%
It's gone too far.

1134
01:51:39.708 --> 01:51:41.083 line:82%
I don't want to fight anymore.

1135
01:51:41.417 --> 01:51:45.208 line:82%
If you want the same then show me a sign.

1136
01:51:45.583 --> 01:51:47.625 line:82%
Just a sign.

1137
01:54:13.167 --> 01:54:15.042 line:82%
Dev. You? Here?

1138
01:54:15.542 --> 01:54:18.667 line:82%
Yeah, I...
just got out of the station.

1139
01:54:19.333 --> 01:54:21.708 line:82%
And these flowers?

1140
01:54:28.792 --> 01:54:29.667 line:82%
For you.

1141
01:55:57.583 --> 01:55:59.333 line:82%
Flowers have their own language

1142
01:56:02.000 --> 01:56:06.083 line:82%
they say so much silently. Right?

1143
01:56:19.375 --> 01:56:22.917 line:82%
I asked for just one sign.
And got so many.

1144
01:56:41.958 --> 01:56:43.625 line:82%
Where's Arjun?

1145
01:56:44.917 --> 01:56:46.542 line:82%
He must have gone to his violin class.
Right?

1146
01:56:48.417 --> 01:56:50.000 line:82%
He's quit the violin.

1147
01:56:50.958 --> 01:56:54.042 line:82%
Quit violin? Why?

1148
01:56:55.375 --> 01:56:59.333 line:82%
He thinks his violin
is the reason for our fights.

1149
01:57:25.875 --> 01:57:27.833 line:82%
What an idiot I have given birth to?

1150
01:57:34.875 --> 01:57:36.500 line:82%
There's no reason to say sorry.

1151
01:57:37.125 --> 01:57:38.333 line:82%
There's no reason to quit violin

1152
01:57:38.417 --> 01:57:39.625 line:82%
and there is absolutely
no reason to play football.

1153
01:57:49.500 --> 01:57:50.833 line:82%
Anyone can play the football.

1154
01:57:51.500 --> 01:57:52.750 line:82%
Even I can.

1155
01:58:09.167 --> 01:58:11.292 line:82%
You can play violin as much
as you want from today.

1156
01:58:12.042 --> 01:58:14.708 line:82%
Play it day and night.
I won't say anything.

1157
01:58:20.875 --> 01:58:25.917 line:82%
Because now I have this.

1158
01:58:47.875 --> 01:58:50.375 line:82%
We will make an eleven member team.

1159
01:58:50.667 --> 01:58:52.458 line:82%
You play the violin
in the forward position.

1160
01:58:52.542 --> 01:58:53.875 line:82%
Violin doesn't have a forward.

1161
01:58:55.542 --> 01:58:59.375 line:82%
And our band will be called
Manchester United Philharmonic.

1162
01:59:31.208 --> 01:59:32.417 line:82%
Rishi, all this.

1163
01:59:40.667 --> 01:59:42.208 line:82%
I cleaned the entire house.

1164
01:59:42.708 --> 01:59:47.875 line:82%
It took three hours.
The food's ready, really.

1165
01:59:48.708 --> 01:59:51.917 line:82%
With these very hands I phoned
and called for food.

1166
01:59:58.708 --> 01:59:59.667 line:82%
This whole weekend.

1167
02:00:02.083 --> 02:00:05.417 line:82%
You and me.
All day and all night.

1168
02:00:07.333 --> 02:00:12.333 line:82%
For hours, with each other...

1169
02:00:13.917 --> 02:00:17.917 line:82%
discuss things.
Whatever you want we shall discuss.

1170
02:00:23.958 --> 02:00:24.917 line:82%
For that night.

1171
02:00:28.417 --> 02:00:30.458 line:82%
Sometimes you make mistakes in love.

1172
02:00:50.000 --> 02:00:51.478 line:82%
Who are you talking to?

1173
02:01:01.958 --> 02:01:04.375 line:82%
Sorry, I couldn't take your calls.

1174
02:01:04.542 --> 02:01:06.417 line:82%
-Rishi was with me the whole weekend--
-Don't worry. It's alright.

1175
02:01:06.667 --> 02:01:08.125 line:82%
I tried only once.

1176
02:01:09.292 --> 02:01:11.125 line:82%
But I got 15 missed calls.

1177
02:01:11.458 --> 02:01:13.375 line:82%
The numbers get dialed accidentally.

1178
02:01:14.333 --> 02:01:15.458 line:82%
How was the weekend?

1179
02:01:15.833 --> 02:01:19.292 line:82%
Very good.
I spent a lot of time with Rhea and Arjun.

1180
02:01:19.375 --> 02:01:20.458 line:82%
It was fun.

1181
02:01:25.083 --> 02:01:27.708 line:82%
We even went shopping.
Rhea bought a lovely dress.

1182
02:01:29.750 --> 02:01:33.333 line:82%
-Rhea looked very good in it.
-Rhea is very beautiful.

1183
02:01:33.750 --> 02:01:37.250 line:82%
She looks good in anything she wears.
So what did you do today?

1184
02:01:37.583 --> 02:01:38.625 line:82%
Same as every day.

1185
02:01:38.792 --> 02:01:42.750 line:82%
I had lunch with George Bush
and now I'm off for coffee with Madonna.

1186
02:01:45.208 --> 02:01:48.833 line:82%
I don't know what your problem is
but I don't want to fight with you.

1187
02:01:49.083 --> 02:01:50.792 line:82%
Anyway, I'm going out with Rishi.

1188
02:01:52.458 --> 02:01:53.583 line:82%
There seems to be a sudden
love for Rishi?

1189
02:01:58.208 --> 02:02:00.718 line:82%
So, Rishi is taking you to meet
the rest of his family at the zoo?

1190
02:02:00.778 --> 02:02:02.792 line:82%
Rishi is taking me to the ballet...

1191
02:02:03.292 --> 02:02:06.167 line:82%
Ballet? Where men dance without underwear?
Rishi likes all that stuff?

1192
02:02:06.250 --> 02:02:07.958 line:82%
Not Rishi, I like ballet.

1193
02:02:11.958 --> 02:02:13.542 line:82%
You like strange things.

1194
02:02:13.750 --> 02:02:16.250 line:82%
Yeah, nothing
can be more strange than you.

1195
02:02:22.708 --> 02:02:25.083 line:82%
-Dev, I hope you are well.
-I am. Why?

1196
02:02:25.375 --> 02:02:26.750 line:82%
First the flowers, now the ballet.

1197
02:02:45.375 --> 02:02:49.750 line:82%
Hey, Rhea.
Are you following me?

1198
02:02:51.667 --> 02:02:53.583 line:82%
But I'm following your wife for sure.

1199
02:03:02.292 --> 02:03:04.167 line:82%
So even you have come here
to appease your wife?

1200
02:03:21.292 --> 02:03:22.667 line:82%
It's Dev's choice.

1201
02:03:24.583 --> 02:03:28.500 line:82%
You look beautiful, too.
But a little less than Rhea.

1202
02:03:30.542 --> 02:03:33.292 line:82%
Just the way you look a little less
handsome than Rishi.

1203
02:03:41.417 --> 02:03:43.333 line:82%
Dev, you need to be
taken to the doctor tomorrow for sure.

1204
02:06:31.083 --> 02:06:34.958 line:82%
What were we doing?
What were we doing last night?

1205
02:06:35.917 --> 02:06:37.917 line:82%
We were playing with their feelings.

1206
02:06:39.292 --> 02:06:41.792 line:82%
For the first time I felt hatred
for myself.

1207
02:06:42.458 --> 02:06:43.667 line:82%
How could I do this to Rishi?

1208
02:06:43.958 --> 02:06:45.542 line:82%
Feeling bad for him?

1209
02:06:45.792 --> 02:06:47.208 line:82%
You must have felt guilty last night, too.

1210
02:06:48.083 --> 02:06:50.375 line:82%
So what did you do
to get rid of your guilt?

1211
02:06:51.583 --> 02:06:55.167 line:82%
What did you do?
Did you allow him to touch you?

1212
02:07:01.667 --> 02:07:06.167 line:82%
Did he touch you here?
Here, here. Tell me?

1213
02:07:07.375 --> 02:07:08.958 line:82%
You think I don't feel bad?

1214
02:07:09.250 --> 02:07:12.625 line:82%
That my love spends nights with
someone else? But I bear it.

1215
02:07:12.708 --> 02:07:16.208 line:82%
I can't bear it... I can't bear it.

1216
02:07:16.458 --> 02:07:20.167 line:82%
You will have to.
Because our relationship is a dream

1217
02:07:20.583 --> 02:07:23.750 line:82%
That shatters every time we reach home.
And that's the truth.

1218
02:07:23.875 --> 02:07:29.125 line:82%
No, I can't accept this truth.
I can't bear.

1219
02:07:29.833 --> 02:07:33.083 line:82%
I can't bear it.
I can't bear to see you.

1220
02:07:34.333 --> 02:07:37.500 line:82%
You are mine. Just mine.

1221
02:07:38.208 --> 02:07:40.375 line:82%
Then how come he has a greater right.

1222
02:07:41.417 --> 02:07:43.917 line:82%
Your heart is mine but you have his name.

1223
02:07:44.583 --> 02:07:48.292 line:82%
I can't bear it. You are mine.

1224
02:07:48.375 --> 02:07:49.833 line:82%
Dev, what are you doing?

1225
02:08:10.292 --> 02:08:11.958 line:82%
Marriage is a beautiful relationship.

1226
02:08:12.792 --> 02:08:16.125 line:82%
It gives you that special someone
who you trust more than yourself.

1227
02:08:59.875 --> 02:09:02.042 line:82%
Rishi, I don't know who's following whom.

1228
02:09:06.292 --> 02:09:08.917 line:82%
But only you and me know
the real reason why we are celebrating.

